September 2 at 12:21 PM ¬∑

Do you need an extra mask for your child? Donated masks range in size from very small (for our preK kids) to adult size (for our high schoolers). We've got some really cool patterns to choose from as well.
You can pick them up at the West Liberty Food Pantry (You don't need to be a food pantry client to pick up some of the donated masks)

This will be an ongoing process. As long as we are getting donations, we will be sharing them through the food pantry.

post_text: We just received an update from our sales representative concerning the delivery of the 570 additional Chromebooks that we ordered earlier this summer. He is being told at this time that all 570 Chromebooks will arrive sometime in October. He noted that most of the school districts that he is working with across the country are in a similar situation. We will be utilizing all of the Chromebooks that we have in stock right now, however, we are very aware that we will be short until this shipment arrives. We wanted to be sure to communicate this information to the public as soon as possible. Please know that we are already working with our teachers on a plan B for Hybrid virtual weeks so that we will be covered until our additional Chromebooks arrive.

post_text:
Revised 2020 Comet Football Schedule
The Iowa High School Athletic Association has revised the 2020 football schedule. At this time, we are waiting to finalize the schedule, however, we can announce the following dates:

September 11 vs. Maquoketa
September 18 @ Tipton
September 25 vs. Camanche
October 2 @ Anamosa
October 9 vs. Monticello
October 16 - Play-offs begin

We will release more information next week once the week 1 (August 28) and 2 (September 4) games are confirmed. For more information about the 2020 football season, please visit https://www.iahsaa.org/football-2020-revised-schedule/

Thank you Hills Bank for the Classroom Cash program! Thank you to all of the Hills Bank customers who choose to have their Classroom Cash earnings go to West Liberty Community School District each time they make a purchase with their Hills Bank debit card!
